Package tech.gitpicard.jcalc

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Function
    Implement a call to a function from an expression.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JCalculator
    Evaluates expressions from plain-text source using an abstract syntax tree to support advanced expression syntax such as function calls.
    Lexer
    Used to pick out context free tokens from a source expression.
    Parser
    Builds an abstract syntax tree from a lexer that will feed the parser tokens.
    Token
    Represents a literal in the stream of source text.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Operation
    A enumeration of the possible mathematical operations that can be performed with operators and not function calls.
    TokenType
    An enumeration of all the token types that can be encountered in an expression.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EvalException
    An exception occurring at runtime due to an illegal operation.
    SyntaxException
    An exception caused by illegal expression syntax.
